article.description: Monica Wright scored a game-high 28 points to lift Virginia (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) past Monmouth, 73-45 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Wright's 28 lead No. 15 Virginia past Monmouth
article.linkText: Wright scores 28 as No. 15 Virginia prevails
article.story:
CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. -- Monica Wright scored a game-high 28 points to lift Virginia (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) past Monmouth, 73-45 on Thursday night.

Wright finished 13 of 16 from the field, and forward Lyndra Littles finished with 17 points in her first appearance of the season for the Cavaliers (8-2). Chelsea Shine added 14 points, seven rebounds and four blocks.

Jennifer Bender led the Hawks (4-6) with 16 points and eight rebounds. Marisa Jimenez added 11 points.

Monmouth was 15-of-51 shooting for the game, the poor offensive execution allowing Virginia to take a 20-6 lead about 8 minutes in. The Cavaliers never pushed the lead to 41-21 by halftime.

Wright paced the Cavaliers' offense early, scoring 19 of her points in the opening half.
